review_blob: 2015 22oz bottle.Pours super black with very small head. Nose is brown sugar,coffee, chocolate, vanilla, alcohol. Taste is very similar coffee, chocolate, raisin, vanilla, with some barrel. Cant really taste the alcohol. This is a great coffee stout and readily available everywhere in MI
beer_name: Griffin Claw Coffee Bourbon Imperial Stout

review_blob: Theres a reason this is called Bomb! This comes off the nose as chocolate, coffee, some spice (floral,), maybe some nuts. The taste is bonkers. It hits everything it says it does. A great beer and definitely worth the price of admission.
By far the best IPA ive ever had. Better then Pliny. This IPA is extra juicy and just worth the price in trade

2012-14. Very smooth. Alcohol was hidden in all of it. The nose is very chocolate, vanilla, dark fruit, some barrel and coffee. Taste is just wow. Has all flavors from the nose. This beer is complex but extremely drinkable. Definitely a beer to share due to the geatness and high abv.
